BITMASKING::
- we use binary nums instead of set
- set is slower whereas bitmasking is faster
- for eg: col = 010010 -> means col 1 & 4 occupied
  col:   5 4 3 2 1 0
  bits:  0 1 0 0 1 0
we use:
        if (cols >> col) & 1:
"cols>>col" will shift the num and "& 1" extracts the last digit from shifted number.
> for placing the queen we do:
        cols = cols | (1 << col)
> for removing the queen:
        cols = cols & ~(1 << col)

== Final Pattern
```
def backtrack(row, cols, diag1, diag2):
    if row == n:
        return 1
    count = 0
    for col in range(n):
        if (cols >> col) & 1:
            continue
        
        if (diag1 >> (row + col)) & 1:
            continue
        
        if (diag2 >> (row - col + n)) & 1:
            continue
        
        count += backtrack(
            row + 1,
            cols | (1 << col),
            diag1 | (1 << (row + col)),
            diag2 | (1 << (row - col + n))
        )
    
    return count
```
